### Async Data Fetching in Next.js not-found Server Component

Source: https://github.com/vercel/next.js/blob/canary/docs/01-app/03-api-reference/03-file-conventions/not-found.mdx

Creates an async not-found Server Component that fetches headers and site data to display custom 404 content. The component retrieves the host domain from request headers and uses it to fetch site-specific data. This approach works for route-specific not-found pages in the app directory.

```typescript
import Link from 'next/link'
import { headers } from 'next/headers'

export default async function NotFound() {
  const headersList = await headers()
  const domain = headersList.get('host')
  const data = await getSiteData(domain)
  return (
    <div>
      <h2>Not Found: {data.name}</h2>
      <p>Could not find requested resource</p>
      <p>
        View <Link href="/blog">all posts</Link>
      </p>
    </div>
  )
}
```

