### Header, Cookie, and Query Matching > Conditional Redirect Conditions

Source: https://github.com/vercel/next.js/blob/canary/docs/01-app/03-api-reference/05-config/01-next-config-js/redirects.mdx

The `has` and `missing` fields enable conditional redirects based on HTTP headers, cookies, query parameters, or host values. The `has` field specifies conditions that must be present for the redirect to apply, while the `missing` field specifies conditions that must not be present. Both the source path and all `has` conditions must match, and all `missing` conditions must not match for the redirect to be executed. This allows for sophisticated redirect logic that responds to request metadata beyond just the URL path.

